This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with the construction of adversarial examples that can fool object detectors. It also involves the use of deep learning models such as Faster RCNN and YOLO, which are commonly used in computer vision tasks. 

The paper also involves the use of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) techniques to construct the adversarial examples. 

As the paper involves the evaluation of the effectiveness of the adversarial examples, it is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. 

Since the paper discusses the potential security hazards that could arise from the use of adversarial examples, it could also belong to the cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-category. 

Finally, as the paper involves the use of smart vehicles, it could also belong to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category.
